      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study (coarse 0.8 mm, medium 0.5 mm, fine 0.3 mm element size at critical screw-rod interface) was performed. QoI changes between medium and fine meshes were 0.9%, 1.3%, and 0.7% for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm respectively. GCI values all below 3%. Medium mesh adopted for production runs."
