    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-level factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 specifies a single standardized test configuration for this device class and the regulatory submission does not require multi-condition validation. All three primary QoIs satisfy both quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible to support the intended regulatory use. Note: this package conforms to ProfileMinimal; the digital signature workflow is pending organizational PKI provisioning and has not yet been applied to this record.",
